      • isMatchQueryDirty

        public boolean isMatchQueryDirty()
        Checks if the query is dirty. Returning true means that the match query parameters have been updated and a new request must be sent to obtain the matchlists. False means that a call to getMatchQuery() or getMatchQueryEntities() will return immediately.
        Returns:
        Whether the query is dirty.

      • setMatchQueryTimeRange

        public boolean setMatchQueryTimeRange(Long beginTime,
                                      Long endTime)
        Sets the begin and end time for a match query. Both bounds are inclusive.
        setMatchQueryTimeRange(null, null) will remove the time restriction.
        Parameters:
        beginTime - Begin time in epoch milliseconds, or null to remove.
        endTime - End time in epoch milliseconds, or null to remove.
        Returns:
        Whether the query is dirty.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If beginTime is greater than endTime.

      • setMatchQueryChampions

        public boolean setMatchQueryChampions(List<Integer> champions)
        Sets the champions for a match query.
        Parameters:
        champions - Champions that summoner played in queried matches, or null to remove.
        Returns:
        Whether the query is dirty.

      • setMatchQuerySeasons

        public boolean setMatchQuerySeasons(List<Integer> seasons)
        Sets the seasons for a match query.
        Parameters:
        seasons - Seasons to return matches from.
        Returns:
        Whether the query is dirty.

      • setMatchQueryIndexRange

        public boolean setMatchQueryIndexRange(Integer beginIndex,
                                       Integer endIndex)
        Sets the begin and end indices for a match query. Range bounds are inclusive (probably).
        setMatchQueryIndexRange(null, null) will remove the index restriction.
        Parameters:
        beginIndex - Begin index, or null to remove.
        endIndex - End index, or null to remove.
        Returns:
        Whether the query is dirty.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If beginIndex is greater than endIndex.

      • getMatchQueryEntitiesAsync

        public CompletableFuture<List<MatchEntity>> getMatchQueryEntitiesAsync()
        Queries matches with the parameters set by setMatchQuery*** methods. Only sends a new request if the query is marked dirty (parameters have been updated).

        May returned cached instances as described in EntityApi.getMatch(com.mingweisamuel.zyra.enums.Region, long, java.lang.String).
        Returns:
        A CompletableFuture of the List of MatchEntities.
